Scotland's biggest music festival is about to get under way.TRNSMT 2024 will take over Glasgow for three days, featuring the likes of Liam Gallagher, the Last Dinner Party and Gerry Cinnamon.If you're not going, highlights will be airing throughout the weekend on BBC One and BBC Scotland, full sets from many acts will be available via iPlayer and Radio Scotland and Radio 1 will be broadcasting from the festival.To help you plan, here is the line-up for each stage, and the times they are expected to be on.
